        Entry(org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Composite entryParent,
     java.lang.Object entryLayoutData,
     org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Color entryBackgroundColor,
     java.lang.String labelText,
     org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Color labelForegroundColor,
     org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Color labelBackgroundColor,
     org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Font labelFont,
     org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Color textForegroundColor,
     org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Color textBackgroundColor,
     org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Font textFont)
        Adds an Entry within the input Composite. Has a Label on the left and a Text (textfield) on the right. The Label is left-aligned with initial text "init". The Text is left-aligned, uneditable, and has a predefined minimum width.
        Parameters:
        entryParent - The Composite to contain this.
        entryLayoutData - The desired LayoutData of this.
        entryBackgroundColor - the desired background of this
        labelText - The desired text of the Label.
        labelForegroundColor - The desired foreground of the Label.
        labelBackgroundColor - The desired background of the Label.
        labelFont - The desired Font of the Label.
        textForegroundColor - The desired foreground of the Text.
        textBackgroundColor - The desired background of the Text.
        textFont - The desired Font of the Text.
